193 struct _cuda_device_id *gpgpu_context::GPGPUSim_Init() {
194  _cuda_device_id *the_device = the_gpgpusim->the_cude_device;
195  if (!the_device) {
196  gpgpu_sim *the_gpu = gpgpu_ptx_sim_init_perf();
197 
198  cudaDeviceProp *prop = (cudaDeviceProp *)calloc(sizeof(cudaDeviceProp), 1);
199  snprintf(prop->name, 256, "GPGPU-Sim_v%s", g_gpgpusim_version_string);
200  prop->major = the_gpu->compute_capability_major();
201  prop->minor = the_gpu->compute_capability_minor();
202  prop->totalGlobalMem = 0x80000000 /* 2 GB */;
203  prop->memPitch = 0;
204  if (prop->major >= 2) {
205  prop->maxThreadsPerBlock = 1024;
206  prop->maxThreadsDim[0] = 1024;
207  prop->maxThreadsDim[1] = 1024;
208  } else {
209  prop->maxThreadsPerBlock = 512;
210  prop->maxThreadsDim[0] = 512;
211  prop->maxThreadsDim[1] = 512;
212  }
213 
214  prop->maxThreadsDim[2] = 64;
215  prop->maxGridSize[0] = 0x40000000;
216  prop->maxGridSize[1] = 0x40000000;
217  prop->maxGridSize[2] = 0x40000000;
218  prop->totalConstMem = 0x40000000;
219  prop->textureAlignment = 0;
220  // * TODO: Update the .config and xml files of all GPU config files
221  // with new value of sharedMemPerBlock and regsPerBlock
222  prop->sharedMemPerBlock = the_gpu->shared_mem_per_block();
223 #if (CUDART_VERSION > 5050)
224  prop->regsPerMultiprocessor = the_gpu->num_registers_per_core();
225  prop->sharedMemPerMultiprocessor = the_gpu->shared_mem_size();
226 #endif
227  prop->sharedMemPerBlock = the_gpu->shared_mem_per_block();
228  prop->regsPerBlock = the_gpu->num_registers_per_block();
229  prop->warpSize = the_gpu->wrp_size();
230  prop->clockRate = the_gpu->shader_clock();
231 #if (CUDART_VERSION >= 2010)
232  prop->multiProcessorCount = the_gpu->get_config().num_shader();
233 #endif
234 #if (CUDART_VERSION >= 4000)
235  prop->maxThreadsPerMultiProcessor = the_gpu->threads_per_core();
236 #endif
237  the_gpu->set_prop(prop);
238  the_gpgpusim->the_cude_device = new _cuda_device_id(the_gpu);
239  the_device = the_gpgpusim->the_cude_device;
240  }
241  start_sim_thread(1);
242  return the_device;
243 }
244 
245 CUctx_st *GPGPUSim_Context(gpgpu_context *ctx) {
246  // static CUctx_st *the_context = NULL;
247  CUctx_st *the_context = ctx->the_gpgpusim->the_context;
248  if (the_context == NULL) {
249  _cuda_device_id *the_gpu = ctx->GPGPUSim_Init();
250  ctx->the_gpgpusim->the_context = new CUctx_st(the_gpu);
251  the_context = ctx->the_gpgpusim->the_context;
252  }
253  return the_context;
254 }

256 gpgpu_context *GPGPU_Context() {
257  static gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL;
258  if (gpgpu_ctx == NULL) {
259  gpgpu_ctx = new gpgpu_context();
260  }
261  return gpgpu_ctx;
262 }

264 void ptxinfo_data::ptxinfo_addinfo() {
265  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(gpgpu_ctx);
266  if (!get_ptxinfo_kname()) {
267  /* This info is not per kernel (since CUDA 5.0 some info (e.g. gmem, and
268  * cmem) is added at the beginning for the whole binary ) */
269  print_ptxinfo();
270  context->add_ptxinfo(get_ptxinfo());
271  clear_ptxinfo();
272  return;
273  }
274  if (!strcmp("__cuda_dummy_entry__", get_ptxinfo_kname())) {
275  // this string produced by ptxas for empty ptx files (e.g., bandwidth test)
276  clear_ptxinfo();
277  return;
278  }
279  print_ptxinfo();
280  context->add_ptxinfo(get_ptxinfo_kname(), get_ptxinfo());
281  clear_ptxinfo();
282 }

284 void cuda_not_implemented(const char *func, unsigned line) {
285  fflush(stdout);
286  fflush(stderr);
287  printf(
288  "\n\nGPGPU-Sim PTX: Execution error: CUDA API function \"%s()\" has not "
289  "been implemented yet.\n"
290  " [$GPGPUSIM_ROOT/libcuda/%s around line %u]\n\n\n",
291  func, __FILE__, line);
292  fflush(stdout);
293  abort();
294 }

296 void announce_call(const char *func) {
297  printf("\n\nGPGPU-Sim PTX: CUDA API function \"%s\" has been called.\n",
298  func);
299  fflush(stdout);
300 }

302 #define gpgpusim_ptx_error(msg, ...) \
303  gpgpusim_ptx_error_impl(__func__, __FILE__, __LINE__, msg, ##__VA_ARGS__)
304 #define gpgpusim_ptx_assert(cond, msg, ...) \
305  gpgpusim_ptx_assert_impl((cond), __func__, __FILE__, __LINE__, msg, \
306  ##__VA_ARGS__)
307 
308 void gpgpusim_ptx_error_impl(const char *func, const char *file, unsigned line,
309  const char *msg, ...) {
310  va_list ap;
311  char buf[1024];
312  va_start(ap, msg);
313  vsnprintf(buf, 1024, msg, ap);
314  va_end(ap);
315 
316  printf("GPGPU-Sim CUDA API: %s\n", buf);
317  printf(" [%s:%u : %s]\n", file, line, func);
318  abort();
319 }
320 
321 void gpgpusim_ptx_assert_impl(int test_value, const char *func,
322  const char *file, unsigned line, const char *msg,
323  ...) {
324  va_list ap;
325  char buf[1024];
326  va_start(ap, msg);
327  vsnprintf(buf, 1024, msg, ap);
328  va_end(ap);
329 
330  if (test_value == 0) gpgpusim_ptx_error_impl(func, file, line, msg);
331 }

346 // sectiontype: 0 for ptx, 1 for elf
347 void addCuobjdumpSection(int sectiontype,
348  std::list<cuobjdumpSection *> &cuobjdumpSectionList) {
349  if (sectiontype)
350  cuobjdumpSectionList.push_front(new cuobjdumpELFSection());
351  else
352  cuobjdumpSectionList.push_front(new cuobjdumpPTXSection());
353  printf("## Adding new section %s\n", sectiontype ? "ELF" : "PTX");
354 }

372 void setCuobjdumpptxfilename(
373  const char *filename, std::list<cuobjdumpSection *> &cuobjdumpSectionList) {
374  printf("Adding ptx filename: %s\n", filename);
375  cuobjdumpSection *x = cuobjdumpSectionList.front();
376  if (dynamic_cast<cuobjdumpPTXSection *>(x) == NULL) {
377  assert(0 &&
378  "You shouldn't be trying to add a ptxfilename to an elf section");
379  }
380  (dynamic_cast<cuobjdumpPTXSection *>(x))->setPTXfilename(filename);
381 }

415 std::string get_app_binary() {
416  char self_exe_path[1025];
417 #ifdef __APPLE__
418  uint32_t size = sizeof(self_exe_path);
419  if (_NSGetExecutablePath(self_exe_path, &size) != 0) {
420  printf("GPGPU-Sim ** ERROR: _NSGetExecutablePath input buffer too small\n");
421  exit(1);
422  }
423 #else
424  std::stringstream exec_link;
425  exec_link << "/proc/self/exe";
426 
427  ssize_t path_length = readlink(exec_link.str().c_str(), self_exe_path, 1024);
428  assert(path_length != -1);
429  self_exe_path[path_length] = '\0';
430 #endif
431 
432  printf("self exe links to: %s\n", self_exe_path);
433  return self_exe_path;
434 }
435 
436 // above func gives abs path whereas this give just the name of application.
437 char *get_app_binary_name(std::string abs_path) {
438  char *self_exe_path;
439 #ifdef __APPLE__
440  // TODO: get apple device and check the result.
441  printf("WARNING: not tested for Apple-mac devices \n");
442  abort();
443 #else
444  char *buf = strdup(abs_path.c_str());
445  char *token = strtok(buf, "/");
446  while (token != NULL) {
447  self_exe_path = token;
448  token = strtok(NULL, "/");
449  }
450 #endif
451  self_exe_path = strtok(self_exe_path, ".");
452  printf("self exe links to: %s\n", self_exe_path);
453  return self_exe_path;
454 }
455 
456 static int get_app_cuda_version() {
457  int app_cuda_version = 0;
458  char fname[1024];
459  snprintf(fname, 1024, "_app_cuda_version_XXXXXX");
460  int fd = mkstemp(fname);
461  close(fd);
462  std::string app_cuda_version_command =
463  "ldd " + get_app_binary() +
464  " | grep libcudart.so | sed 's/.*libcudart.so.\\(.*\\) =>.*/\\1/' > " +
465  fname;
466  system(app_cuda_version_command.c_str());
467  FILE *cmd = fopen(fname, "r");
468  char buf[256];
469  while (fgets(buf, sizeof(buf), cmd) != 0) {
470  std::cout << buf;
471  app_cuda_version = atoi(buf);
472  }
473  fclose(cmd);
474  if (app_cuda_version == 0) {
475  printf("Error - Cannot detect the app's CUDA version.\n");
476  exit(1);
477  }
478  return app_cuda_version;
479 }

488 /*******************************************************************************
489  * Add internal cuda runtime API call to accept gpgpu_context *
490  *******************************************************************************/
491 cudaError_t cudaSetDeviceInternal(int device, gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
492  gpgpu_context *ctx;
493  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
494  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
495  } else {
496  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
497  }
498  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
499  announce_call(__my_func__);
500  }
501  // set the active device to run cuda
502  if (device <= ctx->GPGPUSim_Init()->num_devices()) {
503  ctx->api->g_active_device = device;
504  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
505  } else {
506  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorInvalidDevice;
507  }
508 }
509 
510 cudaError_t cudaGetDeviceInternal(int *device,
511  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
512  gpgpu_context *ctx;
513  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
514  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
515  } else {
516  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
517  }
518  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
519  announce_call(__my_func__);
520  }
521  *device = ctx->api->g_active_device;
522  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
523 }
524 
525 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaDeviceGetLimitInternal(
526  size_t *pValue, cudaLimit limit, gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
527  gpgpu_context *ctx;
528  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
529  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
530  } else {
531  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
532  }
533  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
534  announce_call(__my_func__);
535  }
536  _cuda_device_id *dev = ctx->GPGPUSim_Init();
537  const struct cudaDeviceProp *prop = dev->get_prop();
538  const gpgpu_sim_config &config = dev->get_gpgpu()->get_config();
539  switch (limit) {
540  case 0: // cudaLimitStackSize
541  *pValue = config.stack_limit();
542  break;
543  case 2: // cudaLimitMallocHeapSize
544  *pValue = config.heap_limit();
545  break;
546 #if (CUDART_VERSION > 5050)
547  case 3: // cudaLimitDevRuntimeSyncDepth
548  if (prop->major > 2) {
549  *pValue = config.sync_depth_limit();
550  break;
551  } else {
552  printf("ERROR:Limit %d is not supported on this architecture \n",
553  limit);
554  abort();
555  }
556  case 4: // cudaLimitDevRuntimePendingLaunchCount
557  if (prop->major > 2) {
558  *pValue = config.pending_launch_count_limit();
559  break;
560  } else {
561  printf("ERROR:Limit %d is not supported on this architecture \n",
562  limit);
563  abort();
564  }
565 #endif
566  default:
567  printf("ERROR:Limit %d unimplemented \n", limit);
568  abort();
569  }
570  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
571 }
572 
573 void **cudaRegisterFatBinaryInternal(void *fatCubin,
574  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
575  gpgpu_context *ctx;
576  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
577  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
578  } else {
579  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
580  }
581  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
582  announce_call(__my_func__);
583  }
584 #if (CUDART_VERSION < 2010)
585  printf(
586  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: ERROR ** this version of GPGPU-Sim requires CUDA 2.1 or "
587  "higher\n");
588  exit(1);
589 #endif
590  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
591  static unsigned next_fat_bin_handle = 1;
592  if (context->get_device()->get_gpgpu()->get_config().use_cuobjdump()) {
593  // The following workaround has only been verified on 64-bit systems.
594  if (sizeof(void *) == 4)
595  printf(
596  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: FatBin file name extraction has not been tested on "
597  "32-bit system.\n");
598 
599  // This code will get the CUDA version the app was compiled with.
600  // We need this to determine how to handle the parsing of the binary.
601  // Making this a runtime variable based on the app, enables GPGPU-Sim
602  // compiled with a newer version of CUDA to run apps compiled with older
603  // versions of CUDA. This is especially useful for PTXPLUS execution.
604  // Skip cuda version check for pytorch application
605  std::string app_binary_path = get_app_binary();
606  int pos = app_binary_path.find("python");
607  if (pos == std::string::npos) {
608  // Not pytorch app : checking cuda version
609  int app_cuda_version = get_app_cuda_version();
610  assert(
611  app_cuda_version == CUDART_VERSION / 1000 &&
612  "The app must be compiled with same major version as the simulator.");
613  }
614 
615  // int app_cuda_version = get_app_cuda_version();
616  // assert( app_cuda_version == CUDART_VERSION / 1000 && "The app must be
617  // compiled with same major version as the simulator." );
618  const char *filename;
619 #if CUDART_VERSION < 6000
620  // FatBin handle from the .fatbin.c file (one of the intermediate files
621  // generated by NVCC)
622  typedef struct {
623  int m;
624  int v;
625  const unsigned long long *d;
626  char *f;
627  } __fatDeviceText __attribute__((aligned(8)));
628  __fatDeviceText *fatDeviceText = (__fatDeviceText *)fatCubin;
629 
630  // Extract the source code file name that generate the given FatBin.
631  // - Obtains the pointer to the actual fatbin structure from the FatBin
632  // handle (fatCubin).
633  // - An integer inside the fatbin structure contains the relative offset to
634  // the source code file name.
635  // - This offset differs among different CUDA and GCC versions.
636  char *pfatbin = (char *)fatDeviceText->d;
637  int offset = *((int *)(pfatbin + 48));
638  filename = (pfatbin + 16 + offset);
639 #else
640  filename = "default";
641 #endif
642 
643  // The extracted file name is associated with a fat_cubin_handle passed
644  // into cudaLaunch(). Inside cudaLaunch(), the associated file name is
645  // used to find the PTX/SASS section from cuobjdump, which contains the
646  // PTX/SASS code for the launched kernel function.
647  // This allows us to work around the fact that cuobjdump only outputs the
648  // file name associated with each section.
649  unsigned long long fat_cubin_handle = next_fat_bin_handle;
650  next_fat_bin_handle++;
651  printf(
652  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: __cudaRegisterFatBinary, fat_cubin_handle = %llu, "
653  "filename=%s\n",
654  fat_cubin_handle, filename);
659  assert(fat_cubin_handle >= 1);
660  if (fat_cubin_handle == 1) ctx->api->cuobjdumpInit();
661  ctx->api->cuobjdumpRegisterFatBinary(fat_cubin_handle, filename, context);
662 
663  return (void **)fat_cubin_handle;
664  }
665 #if (CUDART_VERSION < 8000)
666  else {
667  static unsigned source_num = 1;
668  unsigned long long fat_cubin_handle = next_fat_bin_handle++;
669  __cudaFatCudaBinary *info = (__cudaFatCudaBinary *)fatCubin;
670  assert(info->version >= 3);
671  unsigned num_ptx_versions = 0;
672  unsigned max_capability = 0;
673  unsigned selected_capability = 0;
674  bool found = false;
675  unsigned forced_max_capability = context->get_device()
676  ->get_gpgpu()
677  ->get_config()
678  .get_forced_max_capability();
679  if (!info->ptx) {
680  printf(
681  "ERROR: Cannot find ptx code in cubin file\n"
682  "\tIf you are using CUDA 4.0 or higher, please enable "
683  "-gpgpu_ptx_use_cuobjdump or downgrade to CUDA 3.1\n");
684  exit(1);
685  }
686  while (info->ptx[num_ptx_versions].gpuProfileName != NULL) {
687  unsigned capability = 0;
688  sscanf(info->ptx[num_ptx_versions].gpuProfileName, "compute_%u",
689  &capability);
690  printf(
691  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: __cudaRegisterFatBinary found PTX versions for "
692  "'%s', ",
693  info->ident);
694  printf("capability = %s\n", info->ptx[num_ptx_versions].gpuProfileName);
695  if (forced_max_capability) {
696  if (capability > max_capability &&
697  capability <= forced_max_capability) {
698  found = true;
699  max_capability = capability;
700  selected_capability = num_ptx_versions;
701  }
702  } else {
703  if (capability > max_capability) {
704  found = true;
705  max_capability = capability;
706  selected_capability = num_ptx_versions;
707  }
708  }
709  num_ptx_versions++;
710  }
711  if (found) {
712  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: Loading PTX for %s, capability = %s\n",
713  info->ident, info->ptx[selected_capability].gpuProfileName);
714  symbol_table *symtab;
715  const char *ptx = info->ptx[selected_capability].ptx;
716  if (context->get_device()
717  ->get_gpgpu()
718  ->get_config()
719  .convert_to_ptxplus()) {
720  printf(
721  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: ERROR ** PTXPlus is only supported through "
722  "cuobjdump\n"
723  "\tEither enable cuobjdump or disable PTXPlus in your "
724  "configuration file\n");
725  exit(1);
726  } else {
727  symtab = ctx->gpgpu_ptx_sim_load_ptx_from_string(ptx, source_num);
728  context->add_binary(symtab, fat_cubin_handle);
729  ctx->gpgpu_ptxinfo_load_from_string(ptx, source_num, max_capability,
730  context->no_of_ptx);
731  }
732  source_num++;
733  ctx->api->load_static_globals(symtab, STATIC_ALLOC_LIMIT, 0xFFFFFFFF,
734  context->get_device()->get_gpgpu());
735  ctx->api->load_constants(symtab, STATIC_ALLOC_LIMIT,
736  context->get_device()->get_gpgpu());
737  } else {
738  printf(
739  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: warning -- did not find an appropriate PTX in "
740  "cubin\n");
741  }
742  return (void **)fat_cubin_handle;
743  }
744 #else
745  else {
746  printf("ERROR ** __cudaRegisterFatBinary() needs to be updated\n");
747  abort();
748  }
749 #endif
750 }

752 void cudaRegisterFunctionInternal(void **fatCubinHandle, const char *hostFun,
753  char *deviceFun, const char *deviceName,
754  int thread_limit, uint3 *tid, uint3 *bid,
755  dim3 *bDim, dim3 *gDim,
756  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
757  gpgpu_context *ctx;
758  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
759  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
760  } else {
761  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
762  }
763  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
764  announce_call(__my_func__);
765  }
766  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
767  unsigned fat_cubin_handle = (unsigned)(unsigned long long)fatCubinHandle;
768  printf(
769  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: __cudaRegisterFunction %s : hostFun 0x%p, "
770  "fat_cubin_handle = %u\n",
771  deviceFun, hostFun, fat_cubin_handle);
772  if (context->get_device()->get_gpgpu()->get_config().use_cuobjdump())
773  ctx->cuobjdumpParseBinary(fat_cubin_handle);
774  context->register_function(fat_cubin_handle, hostFun, deviceFun);
775 }

777 void cudaRegisterVarInternal(
778  void **fatCubinHandle,
779  char *hostVar, // pointer to...something
780  char *deviceAddress, // name of variable
781  const char *deviceName, // name of variable (same as above)
782  int ext, int size, int constant, int global,
783  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
784  gpgpu_context *ctx;
785  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
786  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
787  } else {
788  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
789  }
790  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
791  announce_call(__my_func__);
792  }
793  printf(
794  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: __cudaRegisterVar: hostVar = %p; deviceAddress = %s; "
795  "deviceName = %s\n",
796  hostVar, deviceAddress, deviceName);
797  printf(
798  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: __cudaRegisterVar: Registering const memory space of %d "
799  "bytes\n",
800  size);
801  if (GPGPUSim_Context(ctx)
802  ->get_device()
803  ->get_gpgpu()
804  ->get_config()
805  .use_cuobjdump())
806  ctx->cuobjdumpParseBinary((unsigned)(unsigned long long)fatCubinHandle);
807  fflush(stdout);
808  if (constant && !global && !ext) {
809  ctx->func_sim->gpgpu_ptx_sim_register_const_variable(hostVar, deviceName,
810  size);
811  } else if (!constant && !global && !ext) {
812  ctx->func_sim->gpgpu_ptx_sim_register_global_variable(hostVar, deviceName,
813  size);
814  } else
815  cuda_not_implemented(__my_func__, __LINE__);
816 }

889 cudaError_t cudaSetupArgumentInternal(const void *arg, size_t size,

893  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
894  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;

897  }

899  announce_call(__my_func__);
900  }
901  gpgpusim_ptx_assert(!ctx->api->g_cuda_launch_stack.empty(),
902  "empty launch stack");
903  kernel_config &config = ctx->api->g_cuda_launch_stack.back();
904  config.set_arg(arg, size, offset);

913 cudaError_t cudaLaunchInternal(const char *hostFun,
914  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
915  gpgpu_context *ctx;
916  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
917  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
918  } else {
919  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
920  }
921  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
922  announce_call(__my_func__);
923  }
924  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
925  char *mode = getenv("PTX_SIM_MODE_FUNC");
926  if (mode) sscanf(mode, "%u", &(ctx->func_sim->g_ptx_sim_mode));
927  gpgpusim_ptx_assert(!ctx->api->g_cuda_launch_stack.empty(),
928  "empty launch stack");
929  kernel_config config = ctx->api->g_cuda_launch_stack.back();
930  {
931  dim3 gridDim = config.grid_dim();
932  dim3 blockDim = config.block_dim();
933  if (gridDim.x * gridDim.y * gridDim.z == 0 ||
934  blockDim.x * blockDim.y * blockDim.z == 0) {
935  // can't launch
936  printf("can't launch a empty kernel\n");
937  ctx->api->g_cuda_launch_stack.pop_back();
938  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorInvalidConfiguration;
939  }
940  }
941  struct CUstream_st *stream = config.get_stream();
942 
943  printf("\nGPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaLaunch for 0x%p (mode=%s) on stream %u\n",
944  hostFun,
945  (ctx->func_sim->g_ptx_sim_mode) ? "functional simulation"
946  : "performance simulation",
947  stream ? stream->get_uid() : 0);
948  kernel_info_t *grid = ctx->api->gpgpu_cuda_ptx_sim_init_grid(
949  hostFun, config.get_args(), config.grid_dim(), config.block_dim(),
950  context);
951  // do dynamic PDOM analysis for performance simulation scenario
952  std::string kname = grid->name();
953  function_info *kernel_func_info = grid->entry();
954  if (kernel_func_info->is_pdom_set()) {
955  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: PDOM analysis already done for %s \n",
956  kname.c_str());
957  } else {
958  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: finding reconvergence points for \'%s\'...\n",
959  kname.c_str());
960  kernel_func_info->do_pdom();
961  kernel_func_info->set_pdom();
962  }
963  dim3 gridDim = config.grid_dim();
964  dim3 blockDim = config.block_dim();
965 
966  gpgpu_t *gpu = context->get_device()->get_gpgpu();
967  checkpoint *g_checkpoint;
968  g_checkpoint = new checkpoint();
969  class memory_space *global_mem;
970  global_mem = gpu->get_global_memory();
971 
972  if (gpu->resume_option == 1 && (grid->get_uid() == gpu->resume_kernel)) {
973  char f1name[2048];
974  snprintf(f1name, 2048, "checkpoint_files/global_mem_%d.txt",
975  grid->get_uid());
976 
977  g_checkpoint->load_global_mem(global_mem, f1name);
978  for (int i = 0; i < gpu->resume_CTA; i++) grid->increment_cta_id();
979  }
980  if (gpu->resume_option == 1 && (grid->get_uid() < gpu->resume_kernel)) {
981  char f1name[2048];
982  snprintf(f1name, 2048, "checkpoint_files/global_mem_%d.txt",
983  grid->get_uid());
984 
985  g_checkpoint->load_global_mem(global_mem, f1name);
986  printf("Skipping kernel %d as resuming from kernel %d\n", grid->get_uid(),
987  gpu->resume_kernel);
988  ctx->api->g_cuda_launch_stack.pop_back();
989  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
990  }
991  if (gpu->checkpoint_option == 1 &&
992  (grid->get_uid() > gpu->checkpoint_kernel)) {
993  printf("Skipping kernel %d as checkpoint from kernel %d\n", grid->get_uid(),
994  gpu->checkpoint_kernel);
995  ctx->api->g_cuda_launch_stack.pop_back();
996  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
997  }
998  printf(
999  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: pushing kernel \'%s\' to stream %u, gridDim= (%u,%u,%u) "
1000  "blockDim = (%u,%u,%u) \n",
1001  kname.c_str(), stream ? stream->get_uid() : 0, gridDim.x, gridDim.y,
1002  gridDim.z, blockDim.x, blockDim.y, blockDim.z);
1003  stream_operation op(grid, ctx->func_sim->g_ptx_sim_mode, stream);
1004  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(op);
1005  ctx->api->g_cuda_launch_stack.pop_back();
1006  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1007 }

1009 cudaError_t cudaMallocInternal(void **devPtr, size_t size,
1010  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1011  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1012  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1013  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1014  } else {
1015  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1016  }
1017  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1018  announce_call(__my_func__);
1019  }
1020  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
1021  *devPtr = context->get_device()->get_gpgpu()->gpu_malloc(size);
1022  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1023  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaMallocing %zu bytes starting at 0x%llx..\n",
1024  size, (unsigned long long)*devPtr);
1025  ctx->api->g_mallocPtr_Size[(unsigned long long)*devPtr] = size;
1026  }
1027  if (*devPtr) {
1028  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1029  } else {
1030  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorMemoryAllocation;
1031  }
1032 }

1034 cudaError_t cudaMallocHostInternal(void **ptr, size_t size,
1035  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1036  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1037  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1038  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1039  } else {
1040  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1041  }
1042  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1043  announce_call(__my_func__);
1044  }
1045  *ptr = malloc(size);
1046  if (*ptr) {
1047  // track pinned memory size allocated in the host so that same amount of
1048  // memory is also allocated in GPU.
1049  ctx->api->pinned_memory_size[*ptr] = size;
1050  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1051  } else {
1052  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorMemoryAllocation;
1053  }
1054 }

1081 cudaError_t cudaHostGetDevicePointerInternal(void **pDevice, void *pHost,
1082  unsigned int flags,
1083  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1084  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1085  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1086  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1087  } else {
1088  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1089  }
1090  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1091  announce_call(__my_func__);
1092  }
1093  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1094  announce_call(__my_func__);
1095  }
1096  // only cpu memory allocation happens in cudaHostAlloc. Linking with device
1097  // pointer to pinned memory happens here.
1098  // TODO: once kernel is executed, the contents in global pointer of GPU must
1099  // be copied back to CPU host pointer!
1100  flags = 0;
1101  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
1102  gpgpu_t *gpu = context->get_device()->get_gpgpu();
1103  std::map<void *, size_t>::const_iterator i =
1104  ctx->api->pinned_memory_size.find(pHost);
1105  assert(i != ctx->api->pinned_memory_size.end());
1106  size_t size = i->second;
1107  *pDevice = gpu->gpu_malloc(size);
1108  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1109  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaMallocing %zu bytes starting at 0x%llx..\n",
1110  size, (unsigned long long)*pDevice);
1111  ctx->api->g_mallocPtr_Size[(unsigned long long)*pDevice] = size;
1112  }
1113  if (*pDevice) {
1114  ctx->api->pinned_memory[pHost] = pDevice;
1115  // Copy contents in cpu to gpu
1116  gpu->memcpy_to_gpu((size_t)*pDevice, pHost, size);
1117  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1118  } else {
1119  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorMemoryAllocation;
1120  }
1121 }
1122 
1123 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaMallocArrayInternal(
1124  struct cudaArray **array, const struct cudaChannelFormatDesc *desc,
1125  size_t width, size_t height __dv(1), gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1126  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1127  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1128  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1129  } else {
1130  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1131  }
1132  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1133  announce_call(__my_func__);
1134  }
1135  unsigned size =
1136  width * height * ((desc->x + desc->y + desc->z + desc->w) / 8);
1137  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
1138  (*array) = (struct cudaArray *)malloc(sizeof(struct cudaArray));
1139  (*array)->desc = *desc;
1140  (*array)->width = width;
1141  (*array)->height = height;
1142  (*array)->size = size;
1143  (*array)->dimensions = 2;
1144  ((*array)->devPtr32) =
1145  (int)(long long)context->get_device()->get_gpgpu()->gpu_mallocarray(size);
1146  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaMallocArray: devPtr32 = %d\n",
1147  ((*array)->devPtr32));
1148  ((*array)->devPtr) = (void *)(long long)((*array)->devPtr32);
1149  if (((*array)->devPtr)) {
1150  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1151  } else {
1152  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorMemoryAllocation;
1153  }
1154 }

1156 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI
1157 cudaMemcpyInternal(void *dst, const void *src, size_t count,
1158  enum cudaMemcpyKind kind, gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1159  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1160  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1161  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1162  } else {
1163  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1164  }
1165  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1166  announce_call(__my_func__);
1167  }
1168  // CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context();
1169  // gpgpu_t *gpu = context->get_device()->get_gpgpu();
1170  if (g_debug_execution >= 3)
1171  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaMemcpy(): devPtr = %p\n", dst);
1172  if (kind == cudaMemcpyHostToDevice)
1173  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(
1174  stream_operation(src, (size_t)dst, count, 0));
1175  else if (kind == cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost)
1176  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(
1177  stream_operation((size_t)src, dst, count, 0));
1178  else if (kind == cudaMemcpyDeviceToDevice)
1179  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(
1180  stream_operation((size_t)src, (size_t)dst, count, 0));
1181  else if (kind == cudaMemcpyDefault) {
1182  if ((size_t)src >= GLOBAL_HEAP_START) {
1183  if ((size_t)dst >= GLOBAL_HEAP_START)
1184  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(stream_operation(
1185  (size_t)src, (size_t)dst, count, 0)); // device to device
1186  else
1187  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(
1188  stream_operation((size_t)src, dst, count, 0)); // device to host
1189  } else {
1190  if ((size_t)dst >= GLOBAL_HEAP_START)
1191  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(
1192  stream_operation(src, (size_t)dst, count, 0));
1193  else {
1194  printf(
1195  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaMemcpy - ERROR : unsupported transfer: host to "
1196  "host\n");
1197  abort();
1198  }
1199  }
1200  } else {
1201  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaMemcpy - ERROR : unsupported cudaMemcpyKind\n");
1202  abort();
1203  }
1204  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1205 }

1212  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;

1270 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaMemcpy2DToArrayInternal(
1271  struct cudaArray *dst, size_t wOffset, size_t hOffset, const void *src,
1272  size_t spitch, size_t width, size_t height, enum cudaMemcpyKind kind,
1273  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1274  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1275  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1276  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1277  } else {
1278  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1279  }
1280  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1281  announce_call(__my_func__);
1282  }
1283  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
1284  gpgpu_t *gpu = context->get_device()->get_gpgpu();
1285  size_t size = spitch * height;
1286  size_t channel_size = dst->desc.w + dst->desc.x + dst->desc.y + dst->desc.z;
1287  gpgpusim_ptx_assert(
1288  ((channel_size % 8) == 0),
1289  "none byte multiple destination channel size not supported (sz=%u)",
1290  channel_size);
1291  unsigned elem_size = channel_size / 8;
1292  gpgpusim_ptx_assert((dst->dimensions == 2),
1293  "copy to none 2D array not supported");
1294  gpgpusim_ptx_assert((wOffset == 0), "non-zero wOffset not yet supported");
1295  gpgpusim_ptx_assert((hOffset == 0), "non-zero hOffset not yet supported");
1296  gpgpusim_ptx_assert((dst->height == (int)height),
1297  "partial copy not supported");
1298  gpgpusim_ptx_assert((elem_size * dst->width == width),
1299  "partial copy not supported");
1300  gpgpusim_ptx_assert((spitch == width), "spitch != width not supported");
1301  if (kind == cudaMemcpyHostToDevice)
1302  gpu->memcpy_to_gpu((size_t)(dst->devPtr), src, size);
1303  else if (kind == cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost)
1304  gpu->memcpy_from_gpu(dst->devPtr, (size_t)src, size);
1305  else if (kind == cudaMemcpyDeviceToDevice)
1306  gpu->memcpy_gpu_to_gpu((size_t)dst->devPtr, (size_t)src, size);
1307  else {
1308  printf(
1309  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaMemcpy2D - ERROR : unsupported cudaMemcpyKind\n");
1310  abort();
1311  }
1312  dst->devPtr32 = (unsigned)(size_t)(dst->devPtr);
1313  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1314 }

1362 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaMemcpyAsyncInternal(
1363  void *dst, const void *src, size_t count, enum cudaMemcpyKind kind,
1364  cudaStream_t stream, gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1365  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1366  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1367  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1368  } else {
1369  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1370  }
1371  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1372  announce_call(__my_func__);
1373  }
1374  struct CUstream_st *s = (struct CUstream_st *)stream;
1375  switch (kind) {
1376  case cudaMemcpyHostToDevice:
1377  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(
1378  stream_operation(src, (size_t)dst, count, s));
1379  break;
1380  case cudaMemcpyDeviceToHost:
1381  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(
1382  stream_operation((size_t)src, dst, count, s));
1383  break;
1384  case cudaMemcpyDeviceToDevice:
1385  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(
1386  stream_operation((size_t)src, (size_t)dst, count, s));
1387  break;
1388  default:
1389  abort();
1390  }
1391  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1392 }

1475 cudaError_t cudaGLMapBufferObjectInternal(void **devPtr, GLuint bufferObj,
1476  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1477  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1478  announce_call(__my_func__);
1479  }
1480 #ifdef OPENGL_SUPPORT
1481  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1482  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1483  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1484  } else {
1485  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1486  }
1487  GLint buffer_size = 0;
1488  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
1489 
1490  glbmap_entry_t *p = ctx->api->g_glbmap;
1491  while (p && p->m_bufferObj != bufferObj) p = p->m_next;
1492  if (p == NULL) {
1493  glBindBuffer(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, bufferObj);
1494  glGetBufferParameteriv(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, GL_BUFFER_SIZE, &buffer_size);
1495  assert(buffer_size != 0);
1496  *devPtr = context->get_device()->get_gpgpu()->gpu_malloc(buffer_size);
1497 
1498  // create entry and insert to front of list
1499  glbmap_entry_t *n = (glbmap_entry_t *)calloc(1, sizeof(glbmap_entry_t));
1500  n->m_next = ctx->api->g_glbmap;
1501  ctx->api->g_glbmap = n;
1502 
1503  // initialize entry
1504  n->m_bufferObj = bufferObj;
1505  n->m_devPtr = *devPtr;
1506  n->m_size = buffer_size;
1507 
1508  p = n;
1509  } else {
1510  buffer_size = p->m_size;
1511  *devPtr = p->m_devPtr;
1512  }
1513 
1514  if (*devPtr) {
1515  char *data = (char *)calloc(p->m_size, 1);
1516  glGetBufferSubData(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, 0, buffer_size, data);
1517  memcpy_to_gpu((size_t)*devPtr, data, buffer_size);
1518  free(data);
1519  printf(
1520  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaGLMapBufferObject %zu bytes starting at 0x%llx..\n",
1521  (size_t)buffer_size, (unsigned long long)*devPtr);
1522  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1523  } else {
1524  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorMemoryAllocation;
1525  }
1526 
1527  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1528 #else
1529  fflush(stdout);
1530  fflush(stderr);
1531  printf(
1532  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: GPGPU-Sim support for OpenGL integration disabled -- "
1533  "exiting\n");
1534  fflush(stdout);
1535  exit(50);
1536 #endif
1537 }

1612 size_t getMaxThreadsPerBlock(struct cudaFuncAttributes *attr,
1613  gpgpu_context *ctx) {
1614  _cuda_device_id *dev = ctx->GPGPUSim_Init();
1615  struct cudaDeviceProp prop;
1616 
1617  prop = *dev->get_prop();
1618 
1619  size_t max = prop.maxThreadsPerBlock;
1620 
1621  if (attr->numRegs && (prop.regsPerBlock / attr->numRegs) < max)
1622  max = prop.regsPerBlock / attr->numRegs;
1623 
1624  if (attr->sharedSizeBytes &&
1625  (prop.sharedMemPerBlock / attr->sharedSizeBytes) < max)
1626  max = prop.sharedMemPerBlock / attr->sharedSizeBytes;
1627 
1628  return max;
1629 }

1631 cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaFuncGetAttributesInternal(
1632  struct cudaFuncAttributes *attr, const char *hostFun,
1633  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1634  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1635  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1636  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1637  } else {
1638  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1639  }
1640  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1641  announce_call(__my_func__);
1642  }
1643  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
1644  function_info *entry = context->get_kernel(hostFun);
1645  if (entry) {
1646  const struct gpgpu_ptx_sim_info *kinfo = entry->get_kernel_info();
1647  attr->sharedSizeBytes = kinfo->smem;
1648  attr->constSizeBytes = kinfo->cmem;
1649  attr->localSizeBytes = kinfo->lmem;
1650  attr->numRegs = kinfo->regs;
1651  if (kinfo->maxthreads > 0)
1652  attr->maxThreadsPerBlock = kinfo->maxthreads;
1653  else
1654  attr->maxThreadsPerBlock = getMaxThreadsPerBlock(attr, ctx);
1655 #if CUDART_VERSION >= 3000
1656  attr->ptxVersion = kinfo->ptx_version;
1657  attr->binaryVersion = kinfo->sm_target;
1658 #endif
1659  }
1660  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1661 }

1663 #if (CUDART_VERSION > 5000)
1664 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI
1665 cudaDeviceGetAttributeInternal(int *value, enum cudaDeviceAttr attr, int device,
1666  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1667  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1668  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1669  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1670  } else {
1671  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1672  }
1673  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1674  announce_call(__my_func__);
1675  }
1676 
1677  const struct cudaDeviceProp *prop;
1678  _cuda_device_id *dev = ctx->GPGPUSim_Init();
1679 
1680  if (device <= dev->num_devices()) {
1681  prop = dev->get_prop();
1682  switch (attr) {
1683  case 1:
1684  *value = prop->maxThreadsPerBlock;
1685  break;
1686  case 2:
1687  *value = prop->maxThreadsDim[0];
1688  break;
1689  case 3:
1690  *value = prop->maxThreadsDim[1];
1691  break;
1692  case 4:

1865 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaBindTextureInternal(
1866  size_t *offset, const struct textureReference *texref, const void *devPtr,
1867  const struct cudaChannelFormatDesc *desc, size_t size __dv(UINT_MAX),
1868  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1869  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1870  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1871  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1872  } else {
1873  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1874  }
1875  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1876  announce_call(__my_func__);
1877  }
1878  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
1879  gpgpu_t *gpu = context->get_device()->get_gpgpu();
1880  printf(
1881  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: in cudaBindTexture: sizeof(struct textureReference) = "
1882  "%zu\n",
1883  sizeof(struct textureReference));
1884  struct cudaArray *array;
1885  array = (struct cudaArray *)malloc(sizeof(struct cudaArray));
1886  array->desc = *desc;
1887  array->size = size;
1888  array->width = size;
1889  array->height = 1;
1890  array->dimensions = 1;
1891  array->devPtr = (void *)devPtr;
1892  array->devPtr32 = (int)(long long)devPtr;
1893  offset = 0;
1894  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: size = %zu\n", size);
1895  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: texref = %p, array = %p\n", texref, array);
1896  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: devPtr32 = %x\n", array->devPtr32);
1897  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: Name corresponding to textureReference: %s\n",
1898  gpu->gpgpu_ptx_sim_findNamefromTexture(texref));
1899  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: ChannelFormatDesc: x=%d, y=%d, z=%d, w=%d\n",
1900  desc->x, desc->y, desc->z, desc->w);
1901  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: Texture Normalized? = %d\n", texref->normalized);
1902  gpu->gpgpu_ptx_sim_bindTextureToArray(texref, array);
1903  devPtr = (void *)(long long)array->devPtr32;
1904  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: devPtr = %p\n", devPtr);
1905  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1906 }

1955 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaLaunchKernelInternal(
1956  const char *hostFun, dim3 gridDim, dim3 blockDim, const void **args,
1957  size_t sharedMem, cudaStream_t stream, gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1958  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1959  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1960  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1961  } else {
1962  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1963  }
1964 
1965  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1966  announce_call(__my_func__);
1967  }
1968  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
1969  function_info *entry = context->get_kernel(hostFun);
1970 #if CUDART_VERSION < 10000
1971  cudaConfigureCallInternal(gridDim, blockDim, sharedMem, stream, ctx);
1972 #endif
1973  for (unsigned i = 0; i < entry->num_args(); i++) {
1974  std::pair<size_t, unsigned> p = entry->get_param_config(i);
1975  cudaSetupArgumentInternal(args[i], p.first, p.second);
1976  }
1977 
1978  cudaLaunchInternal(hostFun);
1979  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
1980 }

1982 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaStreamCreateInternal(
1983  cudaStream_t *stream, gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
1984  gpgpu_context *ctx;
1985  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
1986  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
1987  } else {
1988  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
1989  }
1990  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
1991  announce_call(__my_func__);
1992  }
1993  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: cudaStreamCreate\n");
1994 #if (CUDART_VERSION >= 3000)
1995  *stream = new struct CUstream_st();
1996  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->add_stream(*stream);
1997 #else
1998  *stream = 0;
1999  printf(
2000  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: WARNING: Asynchronous kernel execution not supported "
2001  "(%s)\n",
2002  __my_func__);
2003 #endif
2004  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2005 }

2007 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaStreamDestroyInternal(
2008  cudaStream_t stream, gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
2009  gpgpu_context *ctx;
2010  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
2011  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
2012  } else {
2013  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
2014  }
2015  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2016  announce_call(__my_func__);
2017  }
2018 #if (CUDART_VERSION >= 3000)
2019  // per-stream synchronization required for application using external
2020  // libraries without explicit synchronization in the code to avoid the
2021  // stream_manager from spinning forever to destroy non-empty streams without
2022  // making any forward progress.
2023  stream->synchronize();
2024  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->destroy_stream(stream);
2025 #endif
2026  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2027 }

2029 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaStreamSynchronizeInternal(
2030  cudaStream_t stream, gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
2031  gpgpu_context *ctx;
2032  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
2033  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;

2035  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
2036  }
2037  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2038  announce_call(__my_func__);
2039  }
2040 #if (CUDART_VERSION >= 3000)
2041  if (stream == NULL) ctx->synchronize();
2042  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2043  stream->synchronize();
2044 #else
2045  printf(
2046  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: WARNING: Asynchronous kernel execution not supported "
2047  "(%s)\n",
2048  __my_func__);
2049 #endif
2050  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2051 }

2086 cudaError_t cudaGLUnmapBufferObjectInternal(GLuint bufferObj,
2087  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
2088  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2089  announce_call(__my_func__);
2090  }
2091 #ifdef OPENGL_SUPPORT
2092  gpgpu_context *ctx;
2093  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
2094  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
2095  } else {
2096  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
2097  }
2098  CUctx_st *ctx = GPGPUSim_Context(ctx);
2099  glbmap_entry_t *p = ctx->api->g_glbmap;
2100  while (p && p->m_bufferObj != bufferObj) p = p->m_next;
2101  if (p == NULL) return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorUnknown;
2102 
2103  char *data = (char *)calloc(p->m_size, 1);
2104  memcpy_from_gpu(data, (size_t)p->m_devPtr, p->m_size);
2105  glBufferSubData(GL_ARRAY_BUFFER, 0, p->m_size, data);
2106  free(data);
2107 
2108  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2109 #else
2110  fflush(stdout);
2111  fflush(stderr);
2112  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: support for OpenGL integration disabled -- exiting\n");
2113  fflush(stdout);
2114  exit(50);
2115 #endif
2116 }

2176 CUevent_st *get_event(cudaEvent_t event) {
2177  unsigned event_uid;
2178 #if CUDART_VERSION >= 3000
2179  event_uid = event->get_uid();
2180 #else
2181  event_uid = event;
2182 #endif
2183  event_tracker_t::iterator e = g_timer_events.find(event_uid);
2184  if (e == g_timer_events.end()) return NULL;
2185  return e->second;
2186 }

2188 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaEventRecordInternal(
2189  cudaEvent_t event, cudaStream_t stream, gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
2190  gpgpu_context *ctx;
2191  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
2192  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
2193  } else {
2194  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
2195  }
2196  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2197  announce_call(__my_func__);
2198  }
2199  CUevent_st *e = get_event(event);
2200  if (!e) return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorUnknown;
2201  struct CUstream_st *s = (struct CUstream_st *)stream;
2202  stream_operation op(e, s);
2203  e->issue();
2204  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(op);
2205  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2206 }

2208 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaStreamWaitEventInternal(
2209  cudaStream_t stream, cudaEvent_t event, unsigned int flags,
2210  gpgpu_context *gpgpu_ctx = NULL) {
2211  gpgpu_context *ctx;
2212  if (gpgpu_ctx) {
2213  ctx = gpgpu_ctx;
2214  } else {
2215  ctx = GPGPU_Context();
2216  }
2217  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2218  announce_call(__my_func__);
2219  }
2220  // reference:
2221  // https://www.cs.cmu.edu/afs/cs/academic/class/15668-s11/www/cuda-doc/html/group__CUDART__STREAM_gfe68d207dc965685d92d3f03d77b0876.html
2222  CUevent_st *e = get_event(event);
2223  if (!e) {
2224  printf(
2225  "GPGPU-Sim API: Error at cudaStreamWaitEvent. Event is not created "
2226  ".\n");
2227  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorInvalidResourceHandle;
2228  } else if (e->num_issued() == 0) {
2229  printf(
2230  "GPGPU-Sim API: Warning: cudaEventRecord has not been called on event "
2231  "before calling cudaStreamWaitEvent.\nNothin g to be done.\n");
2232  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2233  }
2234  if (!stream) {
2235  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->pushCudaStreamWaitEventToAllStreams(
2236  e, flags);
2237  } else {
2238  struct CUstream_st *s = (struct CUstream_st *)stream;
2239  stream_operation op(s, e, flags);
2240  ctx->the_gpgpusim->g_stream_manager->push(op);
2241  }
2242  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2243 }

2745  char buf[1024];

2812 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaStreamQuery(cudaStream_t stream) {
2813  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2814  announce_call(__my_func__);
2815  }
2816 #if (CUDART_VERSION >= 3000)
2817  if (stream == NULL) return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorInvalidResourceHandle;
2818  return g_last_cudaError = stream->empty() ? cudaSuccess : cudaErrorNotReady;
2819 #else
2820  printf(
2821  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: WARNING: Asynchronous kernel execution not supported "
2822  "(%s)\n",
2823  __my_func__);
2824  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess; // it is always success because all
2825  // cuda calls are synchronous
2826 #endif
2827 }

2829 /*******************************************************************************
2830  * *
2831  * *
2832  * *
2833  *******************************************************************************/
2834 
2835 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaEventCreate(cudaEvent_t *event) {
2836  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2837  announce_call(__my_func__);
2838  }
2839  CUevent_st *e = new CUevent_st(false);
2840  g_timer_events[e->get_uid()] = e;
2841 #if CUDART_VERSION >= 3000
2842  *event = e;
2843 #else
2844  *event = e->get_uid();
2845 #endif
2846  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2847 }
2848

2859 
2860 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaEventQuery(cudaEvent_t event) {
2861  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2862  announce_call(__my_func__);
2863  }
2864  CUevent_st *e = get_event(event);
2865  if (e == NULL) {
2866  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorInvalidValue;
2867  } else if (e->done()) {
2868  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2869  } else {
2870  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorNotReady;
2871  }
2872 }
2873 
2874 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaEventSynchronize(cudaEvent_t event) {
2875  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2876  announce_call(__my_func__);
2877  }
2878  printf("GPGPU-Sim API: cudaEventSynchronize ** waiting for event\n");
2879  fflush(stdout);
2880  CUevent_st *e = (CUevent_st *)event;
2881  while (!e->done())
2882  ;
2883  printf("GPGPU-Sim API: cudaEventSynchronize ** event detected\n");
2884  fflush(stdout);
2885  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2886 }
2887 
2888 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaEventDestroy(cudaEvent_t event) {
2889  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2890  announce_call(__my_func__);
2891  }
2892  CUevent_st *e = get_event(event);
2893  unsigned event_uid = e->get_uid();
2894  event_tracker_t::iterator pe = g_timer_events.find(event_uid);
2895  if (pe == g_timer_events.end())
2896  return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorInvalidValue;
2897  g_timer_events.erase(pe);
2898  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2899 }
2900 
2901 __host__ cudaError_t CUDARTAPI cudaEventElapsedTime(float *ms,
2902  cudaEvent_t start,
2903  cudaEvent_t end) {
2904  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
2905  announce_call(__my_func__);
2906  }
2907  time_t elapsed_time;
2908  CUevent_st *s = get_event(start);
2909  CUevent_st *e = get_event(end);
2910  if (s == NULL || e == NULL) return g_last_cudaError = cudaErrorUnknown;
2911  elapsed_time = e->clock() - s->clock();
2912  *ms = 1000 * elapsed_time;
2913  return g_last_cudaError = cudaSuccess;
2914 }

2987 // extracts all ptx files from binary and dumps into
2988 // prog_name.unique_no.sm_<>.ptx files
2989 void cuda_runtime_api::extract_ptx_files_using_cuobjdump(CUctx_st *context) {
2990  char command[1000];
2991  char *pytorch_bin = getenv("PYTORCH_BIN");
2992  std::string app_binary = get_app_binary();
2993 
2994  char ptx_list_file_name[1024];
2995  snprintf(ptx_list_file_name, 1024, "_cuobjdump_list_ptx_XXXXXX");
2996  int fd2 = mkstemp(ptx_list_file_name);
2997  close(fd2);
2998 
2999  if (pytorch_bin != NULL && strlen(pytorch_bin) != 0) {
3000  app_binary = std::string(pytorch_bin);
3001  }
3002 
3003  // only want file names
3004  snprintf(command, 1000,
3005  "$CUDA_INSTALL_PATH/bin/cuobjdump -lptx %s | cut -d \":\" -f 2 | "
3006  "awk '{$1=$1}1' > %s",
3007  app_binary.c_str(), ptx_list_file_name);
3008  if (system(command) != 0) {
3009  printf("WARNING: Failed to execute cuobjdump to get list of ptx files \n");
3010  exit(0);
3011  }
3012  if (!gpgpu_ctx->device_runtime->g_cdp_enabled) {
3013  // based on the list above, dump ptx files individually. Format of dumped
3014  // ptx file is prog_name.unique_no.sm_<>.ptx
3015 
3016  std::ifstream infile(ptx_list_file_name);
3017  std::string line;
3018  while (std::getline(infile, line)) {
3019  // int pos = line.find(std::string(get_app_binary_name(app_binary)));
3020  const char *ptx_file = line.c_str();
3021  printf("Extracting specific PTX file named %s \n", ptx_file);
3022  snprintf(command, 1000, "$CUDA_INSTALL_PATH/bin/cuobjdump -xptx %s %s",
3023  ptx_file, app_binary.c_str());
3024  if (system(command) != 0) {
3025  printf("ERROR: command: %s failed \n", command);
3026  exit(0);
3027  }
3028  context->no_of_ptx++;
3029  }
3030  }
3031 
3032  if (!context->no_of_ptx) {
3033  printf(
3034  "WARNING: Number of ptx in the executable file are 0. One of the "
3035  "reasons might be\n");
3036  printf("\t1. CDP is enabled\n");
3037  printf("\t2. When using PyTorch, PYTORCH_BIN is not set correctly\n");
3038  }
3039 
3040  std::ifstream infile(ptx_list_file_name);
3041  std::string line;
3042  while (std::getline(infile, line)) {
3043  // int pos = line.find(std::string(get_app_binary_name(app_binary)));
3044  int pos1 = line.find("sm_");
3045  int pos2 = line.find_last_of(".");
3046  if (pos1 == std::string::npos && pos2 == std::string::npos) {
3047  printf("ERROR: PTX list is not in correct format");
3048  exit(0);
3049  }
3050  std::string vstr = line.substr(pos1 + 3, pos2 - pos1 - 3);
3051  int version = atoi(vstr.c_str());
3052  if (version_filename.find(version) == version_filename.end()) {
3053  version_filename[version] = std::set<std::string>();
3054  }
3055  version_filename[version].insert(line);
3056  }
3057 }

3066 void cuda_runtime_api::extract_code_using_cuobjdump() {
3067  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(gpgpu_ctx);
3068 
3069  // prevent the dumping by cuobjdump everytime we execute the code!
3070  const char *override_cuobjdump = getenv("CUOBJDUMP_SIM_FILE");
3071  char command[1000];
3072  std::string app_binary = get_app_binary();
3073  // Running cuobjdump using dynamic link to current process
3074  snprintf(command, 1000, "md5sum %s ", app_binary.c_str());
3075  printf("Running md5sum using \"%s\"\n", command);
3076  if (system(command)) {
3077  std::cout << "Failed to execute: " << command << std::endl;
3078  exit(1);
3079  }
3080  // Running cuobjdump using dynamic link to current process
3081  // Needs the option '-all' to extract PTX from CDP-enabled binary
3082 
3083  // dump ptx for all individial ptx files into sepearte files which is later
3084  // used by ptxas.
3085  int result = 0;
3086 #if (CUDART_VERSION >= 6000)
3087  extract_ptx_files_using_cuobjdump(context);
3088  return;
3089 #endif
3090  // TODO: redundant to dump twice. how can it be prevented?
3091  // dump only for specific arch
3092  char fname[1024];
3093  if ((override_cuobjdump == NULL) || (strlen(override_cuobjdump) == 0)) {
3094  snprintf(fname, 1024, "_cuobjdump_complete_output_XXXXXX");
3095  int fd = mkstemp(fname);
3096  close(fd);
3097  if (!gpgpu_ctx->device_runtime->g_cdp_enabled)
3098  snprintf(command, 1000,
3099  "$CUDA_INSTALL_PATH/bin/cuobjdump -ptx -elf -sass %s > %s",
3100  app_binary.c_str(), fname);
3101  else
3102  snprintf(command, 1000,
3103  "$CUDA_INSTALL_PATH/bin/cuobjdump -ptx -elf -sass -all %s > %s",
3104  app_binary.c_str(), fname);
3105  bool parse_output = true;
3106  result = system(command);
3107  if (result) {
3108  if (context->get_device()
3109  ->get_gpgpu()
3110  ->get_config()
3111  .experimental_lib_support() &&
3112  (result == 65280)) {
3113  // Some CUDA application may exclusively use kernels provided by CUDA
3114  // libraries (e.g. CUBLAS). Skipping cuobjdump extraction from the
3115  // executable for this case.
3116  // 65280 is the return code from cuobjdump denoting the specific error
3117  // (tested on CUDA 4.0/4.1/4.2)
3118  printf("WARNING: Failed to execute: %s\n", command);
3119  printf(" Executable binary does not contain any GPU kernel.\n");
3120  parse_output = false;
3121  } else {
3122  printf("ERROR: Failed to execute: %s\n", command);
3123  exit(1);
3124  }
3125  }
3126 
3127  if (parse_output) {
3128  printf("Parsing file %s\n", fname);
3129  FILE *cuobjdump_in;
3130  cuobjdump_in = fopen(fname, "r");
3131 
3132  struct cuobjdump_parser parser;
3133  parser.elfserial = 1;
3134  parser.ptxserial = 1;
3135  cuobjdump_lex_init(&(parser.scanner));
3136  cuobjdump_set_in(cuobjdump_in, (parser.scanner));
3137  cuobjdump_parse(parser.scanner, &parser, cuobjdumpSectionList);
3138  cuobjdump_lex_destroy(parser.scanner);
3139  fclose(cuobjdump_in);
3140  printf("Done parsing!!!\n");
3141  } else {
3142  printf("Parsing skipped for %s\n", fname);
3143  }
3144 
3145  if (context->get_device()
3146  ->get_gpgpu()
3147  ->get_config()
3148  .experimental_lib_support()) {
3149  // Experimental library support
3150  // Currently only for cufft
3151 
3152  std::stringstream cmd;
3153  cmd << "ldd " << app_binary
3154  << " | grep $CUDA_INSTALL_PATH | awk \'{print $3}\' > _tempfile_.txt";
3155  int result = system(cmd.str().c_str());
3156  if (result) {
3157  std::cout << "Failed to execute: " << cmd.str() << std::endl;
3158  exit(1);
3159  }
3160  std::ifstream libsf;
3161  libsf.open("_tempfile_.txt");
3162  if (!libsf.is_open()) {
3163  std::cout << "Failed to open: _tempfile_.txt" << std::endl;
3164  exit(1);
3165  }
3166 
3167  // Save the original section list
3168  std::list<cuobjdumpSection *> tmpsl = cuobjdumpSectionList;
3169  cuobjdumpSectionList.clear();
3170 
3171  std::string line;
3172  std::getline(libsf, line);
3173  std::cout << "DOING: " << line << std::endl;
3174  int cnt = 1;
3175  while (libsf.good()) {
3176  std::stringstream libcodfn;
3177  libcodfn << "_cuobjdump_complete_lib_" << cnt << "_";
3178  cmd.str(""); // resetting
3179  cmd << "$CUDA_INSTALL_PATH/bin/cuobjdump -ptx -elf -sass ";
3180  cmd << line;
3181  cmd << " > ";
3182  cmd << libcodfn.str();
3183  std::cout << "Running cuobjdump on " << line << std::endl;
3184  std::cout << "Using command: " << cmd.str() << std::endl;
3185  result = system(cmd.str().c_str());
3186  if (result) {
3187  printf("ERROR: Failed to execute: %s\n", command);
3188  exit(1);
3189  }
3190  std::cout << "Done" << std::endl;
3191 
3192  std::cout << "Trying to parse " << libcodfn.str() << std::endl;
3193  FILE *cuobjdump_in;
3194  cuobjdump_in = fopen(libcodfn.str().c_str(), "r");
3195  struct cuobjdump_parser parser;
3196  parser.elfserial = 1;
3197  parser.ptxserial = 1;
3198  cuobjdump_lex_init(&(parser.scanner));
3199  cuobjdump_set_in(cuobjdump_in, (parser.scanner));
3200  cuobjdump_parse(parser.scanner, &parser, cuobjdumpSectionList);
3201  cuobjdump_lex_destroy(parser.scanner);
3202  fclose(cuobjdump_in);
3203  std::getline(libsf, line);
3204  }
3205  libSectionList = cuobjdumpSectionList;
3206 
3207  // Restore the original section list
3208  cuobjdumpSectionList = tmpsl;
3209  }
3210  } else {
3211  printf(
3212  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: overriding cuobjdump with '%s' (CUOBJDUMP_SIM_FILE is "
3213  "set)\n",
3214  override_cuobjdump);
3215  snprintf(fname, 1024, "%s", override_cuobjdump);
3216  }
3217 }

3220 // TODO: convert this to C++ streams, will be way cleaner
3221 char *readfile(const std::string filename) {
3222  assert(filename != "");
3223  FILE *fp = fopen(filename.c_str(), "r");
3224  if (!fp) {
3225  std::cout << "ERROR: Could not open file %s for reading\n"
3226  << filename << std::endl;
3227  assert(0);
3228  }
3229  // finding size of the file
3230  int filesize = 0;
3231  fseek(fp, 0, SEEK_END);
3232 
3233  filesize = ftell(fp);
3234  fseek(fp, 0, SEEK_SET);
3235  // allocate and copy the entire ptx
3236  char *ret = (char *)malloc((filesize + 1) * sizeof(char));
3237  fread(ret, 1, filesize, fp);
3238  ret[filesize] = '\0';
3239  fclose(fp);
3240  return ret;
3241 }

3250 
3252 std::list<cuobjdumpSection *> cuda_runtime_api::pruneSectionList(
3253  CUctx_st *context) {
3254  unsigned forced_max_capability = context->get_device()
3255  ->get_gpgpu()
3256  ->get_config()
3257  .get_forced_max_capability();
3258 
3259  // For ptxplus, force the max capability to 19 if it's higher or
3260  // unspecified(0)
3261  if (context->get_device()->get_gpgpu()->get_config().convert_to_ptxplus()) {
3262  if ((forced_max_capability == 0) || (forced_max_capability >= 20)) {
3263  printf(
3264  "GPGPU-Sim: WARNING: Capability >= 20 are not supported in "
3265  "PTXPlus\n\tSetting forced_max_capability to 19\n");
3266  forced_max_capability = 19;
3267  }
3268  }
3269 
3270  std::list<cuobjdumpSection *> prunedList;
3271 
3272  // Find the highest capability (that is lower than the forced maximum) for
3273  // each cubin file and set it in cuobjdumpSectionMap. Do this only for ptx
3274  // sections
3275  std::map<std::string, unsigned> cuobjdumpSectionMap;
3276  int min_ptx_capability_found = 0;
3277  for (std::list<cuobjdumpSection *>::iterator iter =
3278  cuobjdumpSectionList.begin();
3279  iter != cuobjdumpSectionList.end(); iter++) {
3280  unsigned capability = (*iter)->getArch();
3281  if (dynamic_cast<cuobjdumpPTXSection *>(*iter) != NULL) {
3282  if (capability < min_ptx_capability_found ||
3283  min_ptx_capability_found == 0)
3284  min_ptx_capability_found = capability;
3285  if (capability <= forced_max_capability || forced_max_capability == 0) {
3286  if ((cuobjdumpSectionMap.find((*iter)->getIdentifier()) ==
3287  cuobjdumpSectionMap.end()) ||
3288  (cuobjdumpSectionMap[(*iter)->getIdentifier()] < capability))
3289  cuobjdumpSectionMap[(*iter)->getIdentifier()] = capability;
3290  }
3291  }
3292  }
3293 
3294  // Throw away the sections with the lower capabilites and push those with the
3295  // highest in the pruned list
3296  for (std::list<cuobjdumpSection *>::iterator iter =
3297  cuobjdumpSectionList.begin();
3298  iter != cuobjdumpSectionList.end(); iter++) {
3299  unsigned capability = (*iter)->getArch();
3300  if (capability == cuobjdumpSectionMap[(*iter)->getIdentifier()]) {
3301  prunedList.push_back(*iter);
3302  } else {
3303  delete *iter;
3304  }
3305  }
3306  if (prunedList.empty()) {
3307  printf(
3308  "Error: No PTX sections found with sm capability that is lower than "
3309  "current forced maximum capability \n minimum ptx capability found = "
3310  "%u, maximum forced ptx capability = %u \n User might want to change "
3311  "either the forced maximum capability from gpgpusim configuration or "
3312  "update the compilation to generate the required PTX version\n",
3313  min_ptx_capability_found, forced_max_capability);
3314  abort();
3315  }
3316  return prunedList;
3317 }
3318 
3320 std::list<cuobjdumpSection *> cuda_runtime_api::mergeMatchingSections(
3321  std::string identifier) {
3322  const char *ptxcode = "";
3323  std::list<cuobjdumpSection *>::iterator old_iter;
3324  cuobjdumpPTXSection *old_ptxsection = NULL;
3325  cuobjdumpPTXSection *ptxsection;
3326  std::list<cuobjdumpSection *> mergedList;
3327 
3328  for (std::list<cuobjdumpSection *>::iterator iter =
3329  cuobjdumpSectionList.begin();
3330  iter != cuobjdumpSectionList.end(); iter++) {
3331  if ((ptxsection = dynamic_cast<cuobjdumpPTXSection *>(*iter)) != NULL &&
3332  strcmp(ptxsection->getIdentifier().c_str(), identifier.c_str()) == 0) {
3333  // Read and remove the last PTX section
3334  if (old_ptxsection != NULL) {
3335  ptxcode = readfile(old_ptxsection->getPTXfilename());
3336  // remove ptx file?
3337  delete *old_iter;
3338  }
3339 
3340  // Append all the PTX from the last PTX section into the current PTX
3341  // section Add 50 to ptxcode to ignore the information regarding
3342  // version/target/address_size
3343  if (strlen(ptxcode) >= 50) {
3344  FILE *ptxfile = fopen((ptxsection->getPTXfilename()).c_str(), "a");
3345  fprintf(ptxfile, "%s", ptxcode + 50);
3346  fclose(ptxfile);
3347  }
3348 
3349  old_iter = iter;
3350  old_ptxsection = ptxsection;
3351  }
3352  // Store all non-PTX sections and PTX sections with non-matching identifiers
3353  else {
3354  mergedList.push_back(*iter);
3355  }
3356  }
3357 
3358  // Store the final PTX section
3359  mergedList.push_back(*old_iter);
3360 
3361  return mergedList;
3362 }
3363 
3365 std::list<cuobjdumpSection *> cuda_runtime_api::mergeSections() {
3366  std::vector<std::string> identifier;
3367  cuobjdumpPTXSection *ptxsection;
3368 
3369  // Add all identifiers present in PTX sections to a vector
3370  for (std::list<cuobjdumpSection *>::iterator iter =
3371  cuobjdumpSectionList.begin();
3372  iter != cuobjdumpSectionList.end(); iter++) {
3373  if ((ptxsection = dynamic_cast<cuobjdumpPTXSection *>(*iter)) != NULL) {
3374  std::string current_id = ptxsection->getIdentifier();
3375 
3376  // If we haven't yet seen a given identifier, add it to the vector
3377  if (std::find(identifier.begin(), identifier.end(), current_id) ==
3378  identifier.end()) {
3379  identifier.push_back(current_id);
3380  }
3381  }
3382  }
3383 
3384  // Call mergeMatchingSections on all identifiers in the vector
3385  for (std::vector<std::string>::iterator iter = identifier.begin();
3386  iter != identifier.end(); iter++) {
3387  cuobjdumpSectionList = mergeMatchingSections(*iter);
3388  }
3389 
3390  return cuobjdumpSectionList;
3391 }

3395 cuobjdumpELFSection *findELFSectionInList(
3396  std::list<cuobjdumpSection *> sectionlist, const std::string identifier) {
3397  std::list<cuobjdumpSection *>::iterator iter;
3398  for (iter = sectionlist.begin(); iter != sectionlist.end(); iter++) {
3399  cuobjdumpELFSection *elfsection;
3400  if ((elfsection = dynamic_cast<cuobjdumpELFSection *>(*iter)) != NULL) {
3401  if (elfsection->getIdentifier() == identifier) return elfsection;
3402  }
3403  }
3404  return NULL;
3405 }

3458 void cuda_runtime_api::cuobjdumpInit() {
3459  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(gpgpu_ctx);
3460  extract_code_using_cuobjdump(); // extract all the output of cuobjdump to
3461  // _cuobjdump_*.*
3462  const char *pre_load = getenv("CUOBJDUMP_SIM_FILE");
3463  if (pre_load == NULL || strlen(pre_load) == 0) {
3464  cuobjdumpSectionList = pruneSectionList(context);
3465  cuobjdumpSectionList = mergeSections();
3466  }
3467 }
3468 
3470 void gpgpu_context::cuobjdumpParseBinary(unsigned int handle) {
3471  CUctx_st *context = GPGPUSim_Context(this);
3472  if (api->fatbin_registered[handle]) return;
3473  api->fatbin_registered[handle] = true;
3474  std::string fname = api->fatbinmap[handle];
3475 
3476  if (api->name_symtab.find(fname) != api->name_symtab.end()) {
3477  symbol_table *symtab = api->name_symtab[fname];
3478  context->add_binary(symtab, handle);
3479  return;
3480  }
3481  symbol_table *symtab;
3482 
3483 #if (CUDART_VERSION >= 6000)
3484  // loops through all ptx files from smallest sm version to largest
3485  std::map<unsigned, std::set<std::string> >::iterator itr_m;
3486  for (itr_m = api->version_filename.begin();
3487  itr_m != api->version_filename.end(); itr_m++) {
3488  std::set<std::string>::iterator itr_s;
3489  for (itr_s = itr_m->second.begin(); itr_s != itr_m->second.end(); itr_s++) {
3490  std::string ptx_filename = *itr_s;
3491  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: Parsing %s\n", ptx_filename.c_str());
3492  symtab = gpgpu_ptx_sim_load_ptx_from_filename(ptx_filename.c_str());
3493  }
3494  }
3495  api->name_symtab[fname] = symtab;
3496  context->add_binary(symtab, handle);
3497  api->load_static_globals(symtab, STATIC_ALLOC_LIMIT, 0xFFFFFFFF,
3498  context->get_device()->get_gpgpu());
3499  api->load_constants(symtab, STATIC_ALLOC_LIMIT,
3500  context->get_device()->get_gpgpu());
3501  for (itr_m = api->version_filename.begin();
3502  itr_m != api->version_filename.end(); itr_m++) {
3503  std::set<std::string>::iterator itr_s;
3504  for (itr_s = itr_m->second.begin(); itr_s != itr_m->second.end(); itr_s++) {
3505  std::string ptx_filename = *itr_s;
3506  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: Loading PTXInfo from %s\n", ptx_filename.c_str());
3507  gpgpu_ptx_info_load_from_filename(ptx_filename.c_str(), itr_m->first);
3508  }
3509  }
3510  return;
3511 #endif
3512 
3513  unsigned max_capability = 0;
3514  for (std::list<cuobjdumpSection *>::iterator iter =
3515  api->cuobjdumpSectionList.begin();
3516  iter != api->cuobjdumpSectionList.end(); iter++) {
3517  unsigned capability = (*iter)->getArch();
3518  if (capability > max_capability) max_capability = capability;
3519  }
3520  if (max_capability > 20)
3521  printf("WARNING: No guarantee that PTX will be parsed for SM version %u\n",
3522  max_capability);
3523  if (max_capability == 0)
3524  max_capability = context->get_device()
3525  ->get_gpgpu()
3526  ->get_config()
3527  .get_forced_max_capability();
3528 
3529  cuobjdumpPTXSection *ptx = NULL;
3530  const char *pre_load = getenv("CUOBJDUMP_SIM_FILE");
3531  if (pre_load == NULL || strlen(pre_load) == 0)
3532  ptx = api->findPTXSection(fname);
3533  char *ptxcode;
3534  const char *override_ptx_name = getenv("PTX_SIM_KERNELFILE");
3535  if (override_ptx_name == NULL or getenv("PTX_SIM_USE_PTX_FILE") == NULL or
3536  strlen(getenv("PTX_SIM_USE_PTX_FILE")) == 0) {
3537  ptxcode = readfile(ptx->getPTXfilename());
3538  } else {
3539  printf(
3540  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: overriding embedded ptx with '%s' "
3541  "(PTX_SIM_USE_PTX_FILE is set)\n",
3542  override_ptx_name);
3543  ptxcode = readfile(override_ptx_name);
3544  }
3545  if (context->get_device()->get_gpgpu()->get_config().convert_to_ptxplus()) {
3546  cuobjdumpELFSection *elfsection = api->findELFSection(ptx->getIdentifier());
3547  assert(elfsection != NULL);
3548  char *ptxplus_str = ptxinfo->gpgpu_ptx_sim_convert_ptx_and_sass_to_ptxplus(
3549  ptx->getPTXfilename(), elfsection->getELFfilename(),
3550  elfsection->getSASSfilename());
3551  symtab = gpgpu_ptx_sim_load_ptx_from_string(ptxplus_str, handle);
3552  printf("Adding %s with cubin handle %u\n", ptx->getPTXfilename().c_str(),
3553  handle);
3554  context->add_binary(symtab, handle);
3555  gpgpu_ptxinfo_load_from_string(ptxcode, handle, max_capability,
3556  context->no_of_ptx);
3557  delete[] ptxplus_str;
3558  } else {
3559  symtab = gpgpu_ptx_sim_load_ptx_from_string(ptxcode, handle);
3560  // if CUOBJDUMP_SIM_FILE is not set, ptx is NULL. So comment below.
3561  // printf("Adding %s with cubin handle %u\n", ptx->getPTXfilename().c_str(),
3562  // handle);
3563  context->add_binary(symtab, handle);
3564  gpgpu_ptxinfo_load_from_string(ptxcode, handle, max_capability,
3565  context->no_of_ptx);
3566  }
3567  api->load_static_globals(symtab, STATIC_ALLOC_LIMIT, 0xFFFFFFFF,
3568  context->get_device()->get_gpgpu());
3569  api->load_constants(symtab, STATIC_ALLOC_LIMIT,
3570  context->get_device()->get_gpgpu());
3571  api->name_symtab[fname] = symtab;
3572 
3573  // TODO: Remove temporarily files as per configurations
3574 }
3575 }

3952 
3954 
3955 int cuda_runtime_api::load_static_globals(symbol_table *symtab,
3956  unsigned min_gaddr,
3957  unsigned max_gaddr, gpgpu_t *gpu) {
3958  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
3959  announce_call(__my_func__);
3960  }
3961  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: loading globals with explicit initializers... \n");
3962  fflush(stdout);
3963  int ng_bytes = 0;
3964  symbol_table::iterator g = symtab->global_iterator_begin();
3965 
3966  for (; g != symtab->global_iterator_end(); g++) {
3967  symbol *global = *g;
3968  if (global->has_initializer()) {
3969  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: initializing '%s' ... ",
3970  global->name().c_str());
3971  unsigned addr = global->get_address();
3972  const type_info *type = global->type();
3973  type_info_key ti = type->get_key();
3974  size_t size;
3975  int t;
3976  ti.type_decode(size, t);
3977  int nbytes = size / 8;
3978  int offset = 0;
3979  std::list<operand_info> init_list = global->get_initializer();
3980  for (std::list<operand_info>::iterator i = init_list.begin();
3981  i != init_list.end(); i++) {
3982  operand_info op = *i;
3983  ptx_reg_t value = op.get_literal_value();
3984  assert((addr + offset + nbytes) <
3985  min_gaddr); // min_gaddr is start of "heap" for cudaMalloc
3986  gpu->get_global_memory()->write(addr + offset, nbytes, &value, NULL,
3987  NULL); // assuming little endian here
3988  offset += nbytes;
3989  ng_bytes += nbytes;
3990  }
3991  printf(" wrote %u bytes\n", offset);
3992  }
3993  }
3994  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: finished loading globals (%u bytes total).\n",
3995  ng_bytes);
3996  fflush(stdout);
3997  return ng_bytes;
3998 }
3999 
4000 int cuda_runtime_api::load_constants(symbol_table *symtab, addr_t min_gaddr,
4001  gpgpu_t *gpu) {
4002  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
4003  announce_call(__my_func__);
4004  }
4005  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: loading constants with explicit initializers... ");
4006  fflush(stdout);
4007  int nc_bytes = 0;
4008  symbol_table::iterator g = symtab->const_iterator_begin();
4009 
4010  for (; g != symtab->const_iterator_end(); g++) {
4011  symbol *constant = *g;
4012  if (constant->is_const() && constant->has_initializer()) {
4013  // get the constant element data size
4014  int basic_type;
4015  size_t num_bits;
4016  constant->type()->get_key().type_decode(num_bits, basic_type);
4017 
4018  std::list<operand_info> init_list = constant->get_initializer();
4019  int nbytes_written = 0;
4020  for (std::list<operand_info>::iterator i = init_list.begin();
4021  i != init_list.end(); i++) {
4022  operand_info op = *i;
4023  ptx_reg_t value = op.get_literal_value();
4024  int nbytes = num_bits / 8;
4025  switch (op.get_type()) {
4026  case int_t:
4027  assert(nbytes >= 1);
4028  break;
4029  case float_op_t:
4030  assert(nbytes == 4);
4031  break;
4032  case double_op_t:
4033  assert(nbytes >= 4);
4034  break; // account for double DEMOTING
4035  default:
4036  abort();
4037  }
4038  unsigned addr = constant->get_address() + nbytes_written;
4039  assert(addr + nbytes < min_gaddr);
4040 
4041  gpu->get_global_memory()->write(
4042  addr, nbytes, &value, NULL,
4043  NULL); // assume little endian (so u8 is the first byte in u32)
4044  nc_bytes += nbytes;
4045  nbytes_written += nbytes;
4046  }
4047  }
4048  }
4049  printf(" done.\n");
4050  fflush(stdout);
4051  return nc_bytes;
4052 }
4053 
4054 kernel_info_t *cuda_runtime_api::gpgpu_cuda_ptx_sim_init_grid(
4055  const char *hostFun, gpgpu_ptx_sim_arg_list_t args, struct dim3 gridDim,
4056  struct dim3 blockDim, CUctx_st *context) {
4057  if (g_debug_execution >= 3) {
4058  announce_call(__my_func__);
4059  }
4060  function_info *entry = context->get_kernel(hostFun);
4061  gpgpu_t *gpu = context->get_device()->get_gpgpu();
4062  /*
4063  Passing a snapshot of the GPU's current texture mapping to the kernel's info
4064  as kernels should use texture bindings present at the time of their launch.
4065  */
4066  kernel_info_t *result =
4067  new kernel_info_t(gridDim, blockDim, entry, gpu->getNameArrayMapping(),
4068  gpu->getNameInfoMapping());
4069  if (entry == NULL) {
4070  printf(
4071  "GPGPU-Sim PTX: ERROR launching kernel -- no PTX implementation found "
4072  "for %p\n",
4073  hostFun);
4074  abort();
4075  }
4076  unsigned argcount = args.size();
4077  unsigned argn = 1;
4078  for (gpgpu_ptx_sim_arg_list_t::iterator a = args.begin(); a != args.end();
4079  a++) {
4080  entry->add_param_data(argcount - argn, &(*a));
4081  argn++;
4082  }
4083 
4084  entry->finalize(result->get_param_memory());
4085  gpgpu_ctx->func_sim->g_ptx_kernel_count++;
4086  fflush(stdout);
4087 
4088  if (g_debug_execution >= 4) {
4089  entry->ptx_jit_config(g_mallocPtr_Size, result->get_param_memory(),
4090  (gpgpu_t *)context->get_device()->get_gpgpu(),
4091  gridDim, blockDim);
4092  }
4093 
4094  return result;
4095 }
